{"key":"processedPost-17177604","value":{"id":17177604,"first":17172271,"last":17177783,"when":1352300654,"utime":"11/07/12 05:04 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />The longer you keep the bark intact(helps retain log moisture level) the longer the log will produce. </blockquote><br />It's not just about moisture, but fruiting surface.&nbsp; The mushrooms form on the bark, not the bare wood.&nbsp; Smack them with a rubber or rawhide mallet if necessary to protect the bark, or pour in some wax to seal the damage if the bark gets torn.<br />Concussion is a well known shiitake pinning trigger.&nbsp; Shiitake also fruit all summer, and many of my best strains such as S75 don't react to a cold shock at all, so I skip it.<br />In addition, shiitake will perform better on sawdust than on whole logs outdoors as well as indoors, so growers should take note.&nbsp; Some of the sawdust blocks below are in their third and fourth years fruiting and only a fraction of original size.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/12-32/437029127-Outdoor_shiitake_with_depleted_substrate3.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/12-32/437029127-thumb_Outdoor_shiitake_with_depleted_substrate3.jpg\"></a> <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/12-32/437029108-thumb_Outdoor_shiitake_with_depleted_substrate2.jpg\"><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/12-32/437029090-Outdoor_shiitake_with_depleted_substrate.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/12-32/437029090-thumb_Outdoor_shiitake_with_depleted_substrate.jpg\"></a> <a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/12-27/163947372-outdoor_shiitake.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank